      "type": "heading",
      "value": "What is Web Storage?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Web Storage allows websites to store data in the browser. It provides two main types: localStorage and sessionStorage."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Types of Web Storage"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "value": {
        "headers": ["Type", "Lifetime", "Storage Limit"],
        "rows": [
          ["localStorage", "Persistent (no expiration)", "~5MB"],
          ["sessionStorage", "Until browser tab is closed", "~5MB"]
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Using localStorage"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "javascript",
      "value": "// Store data\nlocalStorage.setItem('name', 'John');\n\n// Get data\nlet name = localStorage.getItem('name');\n\n// Remove data\nlocalStorage.removeItem('name');\n\n// Clear all\nlocalStorage.clear();"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Using sessionStorage"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "javascript",
      "value": "// Store data\nsessionStorage.setItem('user', 'Alice');\n\n// Get data\nlet user = sessionStorage.getItem('user');"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Storing Objects"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "javascript",
      "value": "const user = { name: 'John', age: 25 };\n\n// Store\nlocalStorage.setItem('user', JSON.stringify(user));\n\n// Retrieve\nconst storedUser = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('user'));"
    },
